240,000 Acres of beautiful Northern California were engulfed in flames. Nearly 19,000 structures, including homes, businesses, a hospital, and schools, were destroyed or severely damaged. The Camp Fire devastated nearly everything in its path. (3/5)

One year ago today, the landscape of Northern California changed dramatically.
